The paper deals with interference cancellation in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of caching schemes to improve network performance also falls under the scope of cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.MM (multimedia). Finally, the analysis of packet loss rate and tradeoffs between caching and wireless resources may also be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) community.
